.SH SHMultiTaperSE
Perform a localized multitaper spectral analysis using spherical cap
windows.
.SH Usage
call SHMultiTaperSE (\f[CR]mtse\f[R], \f[CR]sd\f[R], \f[CR]cilm\f[R],
\f[CR]lmax\f[R], \f[CR]tapers\f[R], \f[CR]taper_order\f[R],
\f[CR]lmaxt\f[R], \f[CR]k\f[R], \f[CR]alpha\f[R], \f[CR]lat\f[R],
\f[CR]lon\f[R], \f[CR]taper_wt\f[R], \f[CR]norm\f[R],
\f[CR]csphase\f[R], \f[CR]exitstatus\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]mtse\f[R] : output, real(dp), dimension (\f[CR]lmax\f[R]\-\f[CR]lmaxt\f[R]+1)
The localized multitaper power spectrum estimate.
.TP
\f[CR]sd\f[R] : output, real(dp), dimension (\f[CR]lmax\f[R]\-\f[CR]lmaxt\f[R]+1)
The standard error of the localized multitaper power spectral estimates.
.TP
\f[CR]cilm\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension (2, \f[CR]lmax\f[R]+1, \f[CR]lmax\f[R]+1)
The spherical harmonic coefficients of the function to be localized.
.TP
\f[CR]lmax\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The spherical harmonic bandwidth of \f[CR]cilm\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]tapers\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension (\f[CR]lmaxt\f[R]+1, \f[CR]k\f[R])
An array of the \f[CR]k\f[R] windowing functions, arranged in columns,
obtained from a call to \f[CR]SHReturnTapers\f[R].
Each window has non\-zero coefficients for a single angular order that
is specified in the array \f[CR]taper_order\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]taper_order\f[R] : input, integer(int32), dimension (\f[CR]k\f[R])
An array containing the angular orders of the spherical harmonic
coefficients in each column of the array \f[CR]tapers\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]lmaxt\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The spherical harmonic bandwidth of the windowing functions in the array
\f[CR]tapers\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]k\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The number of tapers to be utilized in performing the multitaper
spectral analysis.
.TP
\f[CR]alpha\f[R] : input, optional, real(dp), dimension(3)
The Euler rotation angles used in rotating the windowing functions.
\f[CR]alpha(1) = 0\f[R], \f[CR]alpha(2) = \-(90\-lat)*pi/180\f[R],
\f[CR]alpha(3) = \-lon*pi/180\f[R].
Either \f[CR]alpha\f[R] or \f[CR]lat\f[R] and \f[CR]lon\f[R] can be
specified, but not both.
If none of these are specified, the window functions will not be
rotated, and the spectral analysis will be centered at the north pole.
.TP
\f[CR]lat\f[R] : input, optional, real(dp)
The latitude in degrees of the localized analysis.
Either \f[CR]alpha\f[R] or \f[CR]lat\f[R] and \f[CR]lon\f[R] can be
specified but not both.
If none of these are specified, the window functions will not be
rotated, and the spectral analysis will be centered at the north pole.
.TP
\f[CR]lon\f[R] : input, optional, real(dp)
The longitude in degrees of the localized analysis.
Either \f[CR]alpha\f[R] or \f[CR]lat\f[R] and \f[CR]lon\f[R] can be
specified, but not both.
If none of these are specified, the window functions will not be
rotated, and the spectral analysis will be centered at the north pole.
.TP
\f[CR]taper_wt\f[R] : input, optional, real(dp), dimension (\f[CR]k\f[R])
The weights used in calculating the multitaper spectral estimates and
